trend_summary: Across the five images, the central village grows only slightly, while surrounding parcels cycle through crops, pasture and fallow stages. A handful of new houses and farm sheds appear along main roads, and small woodland blocks are selectively cleared at the southern edge. Overall land use stays dominantly agricultural with minimal urbanisation.
notable_changes: Modest residential infill and a few roadside houses added around the village core.
One-to-two new agricultural sheds erected on larger farms west and east of the settlement.
Several eastern crop fields converted to greener pasture, indicating livestock shift.
Patchy woodland thinning observed in the south-western block, expanding arable land.
Field colour variations reveal crop rotation and seasonal harvesting cycles between dates.
